[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare prescription refill bot decomposes into nine logical stages: channel entry, input safety screening, intent classification, identity verification, medication resolution, refill-eligibility evaluation, transactional fulfillment (e-prescribe or clinical routing), output safety screening, and audit logging. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 and 11.2 carry forward; this recipe adds two new ones (clinical-protocol-as-code lifecycle, prescriber co-signature workflow).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── CHANNEL ENTRY ─────────────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient connects through one of the configured         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    channels: web chat widget, in-app chat, SMS,           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    voice (with ASR/TTS), authenticated patient-portal     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    embed]                                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Greeting and disclosure]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Identifies as a chatbot, not a pharmacist or         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      clinician                                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - States the bot's scope (refills of existing          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      maintenance medications; not new prescriptions,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      not dose changes, not controlled substances          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      auto-approval, not clinical advice)                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Offers an immediate path to a human                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Conversation session bootstrap]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generate session_id                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Capture channel, authentication context, and any     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      deep-link parameters (e.g., patient clicked a        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      "request refill" link from the medication-list       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      page in the portal)                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: session_id, channel, auth context]             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── INPUT SAFETY SCREENING ────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Same primitive as recipes 11.1 and 11.2:]              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Crisis detection (preempts everything; a patient     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      who mentions overdose, suicidal ideation, or         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      misuse during a refill conversation is a crisis      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      signal that routes to the crisis pathway)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Prompt-injection detection                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - PHI minimization                                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: input passes / input blocked-with-disposition] │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── INTENT CLASSIFICATION ─────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Map the user's request to one of the bot's intents]    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - request_refill                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - check_refill_status                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - cancel_refill_request                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - medication_question (peripheral question, not        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      a refill action)                                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - medication_change (asking to start, stop, or         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      change therapy; out of scope)                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - clinical_question (out of scope; route to nurse      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      triage)                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - controlled_substance_request (in-scope-but-          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      route-to-clinician; never auto-approved)             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - out_of_scope (other topics; route appropriately)     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: in-scope intent | out-of-scope handoff]        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── IDENTITY VERIFICATION ─────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Same graduated assurance pattern as recipe 11.2,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    with a higher floor for refill-related actions]        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Authenticated session path]                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient is logged into the patient portal            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - The session conveys an authenticated patient_id      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - The bot accepts the patient_id as verified           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Unauthenticated channel path]                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Refills generally require a higher assurance         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      level than scheduling. Many institutions choose      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      to require authenticated sessions for refill         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      actions and to limit unauthenticated paths to        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      status-check intents only.                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - When unauthenticated paths are allowed, the bot      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      uses the same identity verification primitives       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      as recipe 11.2 with stronger confirmation factors    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (e.g., a one-time code rather than last-four-of-     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      phone)                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Step-up authentication for sensitive actions]          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Asking about a controlled-substance medication       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      may require step-up                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Requesting an early refill may require step-up       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: verified patient_id, assurance_level]          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── MEDICATION RESOLUTION ─────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Tool: medication_list_lookup]                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pull the patient's structured medication list        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      from the EHR via FHIR MedicationRequest              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Include the active medications, their doses,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      frequencies, refills-remaining, last-fill dates,     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      prescribing providers, dispensing pharmacies         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Tool: medication_resolution]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Given the patient's free-text descriptor and the     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      medication list, identify the specific medication    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Use the LLM with the medication list as context      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - When ambiguous, ask the patient to clarify           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (e.g., the patient says "the heart pill" and they    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      take both lisinopril and atorvastatin)               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Discontinued-medication handling]                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - When the patient asks for a medication that the      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      chart marks as discontinued, surface the             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      discrepancy, ask the patient to confirm what they    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      are actually taking, and route to clinical staff     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      with the context preserved                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Specialist-medication handling]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - When the medication's prescribing provider is        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      outside the practice (a cardiologist's amiodarone,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      a rheumatologist's methotrexate), surface the        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      prescriber-authority boundary and route to the       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      appropriate office or coordinated-care pathway       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: resolved medication record, or routing         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    decision]                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── REFILL-ELIGIBILITY EVALUATION ─────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Tool: protocol_evaluate]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Inputs: resolved medication record, patient          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      chart context (active diagnoses, allergies,          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      relevant lab values, blood pressure history,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      other medications), the practice's protocol          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      version, and the request context (timing,            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pharmacy, patient-stated context)                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Output: a structured decision with                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - disposition (auto_approve, route_to_prescriber,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        route_with_monitoring_due, route_with_clinical_    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        question, deny_with_reason, controlled_substance_  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        always_route)                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - reasoning (which protocol rules fired and why)     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - data_consulted (which chart elements the           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        protocol read)                                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - protocol_version (stamped on the decision)         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Drug-interaction and contraindication screening]       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Run the resolved medication against the patient's    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      active medication list and documented allergies      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      and conditions                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Use the institution's clinical-decision-support      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      system (typically CDS Hooks against the EHR) or      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      a dedicated drug-interaction database                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Surface findings to the protocol-evaluation step     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Lab reconciliation]                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - When the protocol requires recent monitoring,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      check for the lab result in the chart                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reconcile outside-lab results that may have come     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      through recently (don't fail the request because     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the lab is technically not in the chart yet when     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the patient knows it was drawn)                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: structured eligibility decision with full      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    reasoning attached]                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── TRANSACTIONAL FULFILLMENT ─────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Auto-approve path]                                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool: e_prescribe                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Submits the refill to the dispensing pharmacy      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        through the e-prescribing platform (typically      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        Surescripts)                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Returns the prescription identifier and the        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        transmission status                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool: cosignature_queue                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Adds the auto-approved refill to the prescriber's  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        co-signature queue for asynchronous review         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        (within the institution's SLA, typically 24-72     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        hours)                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool: refill_event_journal                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Writes the durable record of the refill action     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        with the protocol version, reasoning, data         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        consulted, prescriber, dispensing pharmacy         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Route-to-clinician path]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool: clinical_routing                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Packages the request with the bot's reasoning,     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        the data consulted, and any patient context        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        (e.g., the patient said they have been doubling    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        the dose)                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Queues the structured ticket in the appropriate    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        inbox (nurse triage, prescriber inbox, pharmacy    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        coordination, depending on the disposition)       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Returns the queue position and the expected        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        SLA                                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool: refill_event_journal                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Writes the durable record of the routing event     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Deny-with-reason path]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool: refill_event_journal                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Writes the durable record of the denial with       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │        the protocol-driven reasoning                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Conversational response explains the denial          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      transparently and offers next steps                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Failure handling]                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - E-prescribe transmission error: queue for retry,     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      surface the issue to clinical staff, tell the        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      patient honestly                                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pharmacy unreachable: queue for retry, surface       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the issue, ensure the patient is not left thinking   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the refill was sent when it was not                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Co-signature queue write error: the e-prescribe      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      already happened; the co-signature event is queued   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      for retry; the operations dashboard surfaces         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pending co-signature backlog                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: refill action result with full structured      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    audit data]                                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── OUTPUT SAFETY SCREENING ───────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Same primitive as recipes 11.1 and 11.2, with new      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    refill-specific checks]                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Scope filter on generated response (no clinical      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      advice, no dose changes, no medication starts)       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Vendor-managed guardrail layer                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Hallucination check: did the bot tell the patient    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the refill was sent when no e_prescribe call         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      returned success? Did the bot mention a medication   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      that is not on the patient's list? Did the bot       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      claim a lab value that does not match the lab        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tool's result?                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Controlled-substance guardrail: did the bot          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      indicate it was processing a controlled-substance    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      refill? Verify against the protocol-evaluate         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      result and replace with the routing template if      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      so                                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: response cleared for delivery, or replaced     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    with a refusal-and-handoff]                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, LOG, AND TELEMETRY ─────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User utterances (scrubbed of inadvertent PHI)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generated responses                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active protocol version stamped on every             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      eligibility evaluation                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Identity-verification outcome and assurance level    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Refill outcomes (auto_approved, routed, denied,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      failed, abandoned)                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Refill-event journal]                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Durable, separately-governed record of every         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      refill action: the medication, the patient, the      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      protocol version, the decision, the reasoning,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the data consulted, the e-prescribing identifier,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the dispensing pharmacy, the prescribing provider,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the co-signature status                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Retention sized to the institution's medical-        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      record-retention floor                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Refill auto-approval rate per medication class       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Routing rate per disposition                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Median time-to-completion (auto-approved vs          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      routed)                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Co-signature backlog                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Identity-verification failure rate                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool-call failure rate per tool                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices (language, channel,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      authentication path, age cohort)                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled review queue]                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of low-           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      confidence and escalated conversations               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers tag failure modes (medication-resolution   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      error, protocol-evaluation error, routing-           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      disposition error, etc.)                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Clinical-leadership review of auto-approved          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      sample for protocol-application accuracy             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals]      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the refill bot.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **The protocol is a versioned governance artifact.** The clinical refill protocol, encoded as code, is the bot's most consequential institutional asset. It is owned by clinical leadership, not by engineering. Changes go through clinical-leadership review, sandbox testing, and staged rollout. Every protocol-evaluation result records the active protocol version. Every refill action records the protocol version that authorized it. The conversation log, the refill-event journal, and the operational dashboards all reference the protocol version. When the protocol changes, the institution can reconstruct exactly which decisions were made under which version. This is the load-bearing accountability that makes the bot safe enough to delegate routine refills to.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Prescriber co-signature is not optional, but it is asynchronous.** The bot's authority comes from a delegation arrangement with the prescriber. The prescriber retains responsibility for the patient's therapy. The co-signature workflow surfaces auto-approved refills to the prescriber within a defined SLA (typically 24-72 hours). The prescriber can flag any auto-approval for retrospective clinical review. The flagged reviews feed the protocol-improvement loop. The bot's authority is delegated; the prescriber's accountability is preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Controlled-substance handling is a hard architectural floor.** Every layer of the bot has explicit logic for controlled substances: the medication-list-lookup tool returns the controlled-substance schedule, the medication-resolution step flags controlled substances, the protocol-evaluate tool returns "controlled_substance_always_route" for any controlled-substance request, the e-prescribe tool refuses to transmit controlled substances through the bot's auto-approval path, the output safety screening checks for controlled-substance language in the response. The triple defense is intentional. A bot that auto-approves a controlled substance once is a bot that gets the project canceled.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Medication resolution against the patient's list is the safety floor.** The bot does not act on a medication unless the medication is on the patient's list. The medication-resolution tool returns a structured medication record from the list or returns "no match"; in the no-match case, the bot does not guess. This prevents the failure mode where the bot interprets "the white pill" as a medication that the patient does not take, runs the protocol against a wrong record, and produces a wrong action.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Lab reconciliation closes the most common protocol-block escape valve.** The Eleanor failure mode (lab exists but is not yet reconciled into the chart) is so common that the bot's lab-reconciliation step is part of the architecture, not an optional extension. The institution's reconciliation pipeline (recipe 5.6 patterns) is the integration point; the bot's lab-reconciliation tool checks the latest available result, including pending-reconciliation outside-lab results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **The refill-event journal is a separate record class with stricter governance than the conversation log.** Conversations are PHI-relevant and have audit obligations; refill events are clinical-record events and have medical-record-retention obligations. The institution's medical-records team owns the refill-event journal's retention, access, and disclosure-accounting policies, separately from the conversation-log policies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable, with refill-specific metric slices.** Auto-approval rate, time-to-completion, and routing-disposition mix can vary substantially by language, age cohort, channel, and medication class. Equity-relevant disparities (an auto-approval rate that is meaningfully lower for non-English-speaking patients than for English-speaking patients with the same medication and the same protocol-relevant data) is a launch-gate criterion, not a post-launch dashboard.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Compensation operations cover medication actions specifically.** When a refill that should not have happened did happen, the operational team needs to be able to act: contact the patient, contact the pharmacy if the medication has not been picked up, document the event, surface it for clinical review. The compensation path is explicit, audited, and exercised in tabletop drills before launch.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
